body:
| Peter -- A week from today, the Portman campaign will hold their second Super Saturday day of grassroots action! [Have you RSVP'ed](http://www.robportman.com/super_saturday_april?e=aa4131f163f0a23ba616fd24e19c0e92&utm_source=robportman&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=ssapril2&n=1)?

I'll join Rob at his Columbus stop, but he and Jane will be making stops across the state meeting with interns and volunteers and helping contact voters. The campaign has set an ambitious goal of contacting 50,000 voters in a single day, and they will need your help! [Please click here to RSVP and be part of Super Saturday](http://www.robportman.com/super_saturday_april?e=aa4131f163f0a23ba616fd24e19c0e92&utm_source=robportman&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=ssapril2&n=2)!
**[
](http://www.robportman.com/super_saturday_april?e=aa4131f163f0a23ba616fd24e19c0e92&utm_source=robportman&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=ssapril2&n=3)** Since May of last year, the Portman campaign has contacted more than 1.5 million voters as they work to build one of the most impressive grassroots organizations that Ohio has ever seen. On Super Saturday, the campaign's interns, volunteers, and staff will be making calls and knocking on doors across Ohio. Rob and Jane will begin the day in Brecksville, and then Rob will make stops in Toledo, Dayton, and Columbus. Jane will make stops across the state and end the day in Terrace Park. The campaign's offices across the state will have special guests, including Congressmen and statewide elected officials. In this election, Ohio has a choice between moving forward with our pro-growth policies for better wages and more jobs, or returning to Ted Strickland’s failed policies of higher taxes, more regulations, and bigger government. National Democrats have their eyes on Ohio. [Please join us on Super Saturday and help us build an incredible grassroots organization that will help us win in November](http://www.robportman.com/super_saturday_april?e=aa4131f163f0a23ba616fd24e19c0e92&utm_source=robportman&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=ssapril2&n=4)! Sincerely, Chairman Matt Borges[
](http://www.robportman.com/?e=aa4131f163f0a23ba616fd24e19c0e92&utm_source=robportman&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=ssapril2&n=5)Ohio Republican Party
